To reproduce all panels in this figure you need to have reproduced Figure2. In this script the Meta Data is stored in an object named âClinical_datâ.

Panel A

Show the code 
library(Hmisc)
library(reshape2)
library(ggpubr)
##Load needed data...
Clinical_dat<-readRDS("Clinical_dat.rds") #Available upon request.
###Load er1
er1<-readRDS("er1.rds")

###Subset to patients only at first timePoint...
er1_timepoint2<-er1[er1$Num_microbiome_timePoints==2,]
####Take out patients that were profiled both samples after MTX tx
er1_timepoint2<-er1_timepoint2[er1_timepoint2$Microbiome_ID%nin%c("c8ad5a74_2","c8ad5a74_3","c8ad5a74","43235177_2","43235177"),]

er1_timepoint2$Sampling_time<-ifelse(er1_timepoint2$timePoint==2,"Baseline","After")

er1_timepoint2_t<-melt(er1_timepoint2,id.vars = c("Sampling_time","Microbiome_ID"),measure.vars = c("InvSimpson","Observed","Chao1","Shannon"))

er1_timepoint2_t<-dcast(er1_timepoint2_t, variable+Microbiome_ID ~ Sampling_time, value.var = "value",fill = 0,fun.aggregate = sum,drop = T)

p1_div_mtx2<-ggpaired(er1_timepoint2_t[er1_timepoint2_t$variable=="InvSimpson",], cond1 = "Baseline",cond2 = "After", line.color = "black", line.size = 0.4,id = "Microbiome_ID",facet.by = "variable",fill="condition",xlab = "Condition",ylab = "Fecal diversity")+theme_std()+theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90,size=8),axis.title = element_text(face="bold"),plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5,face = "bold",size = 15))+stat_compare_means(paired = TRUE,label = "p.format",vjust=.35)+scale_fill_manual(values = rep(c("steelblue1","steelblue4"),1),labels=c("Baseline","After"))
p1_div_mtx2

ggsave(p1_div_mtx2,filename = "Figure3_panelA.pdf",width = 14,height = 12)

#We need the ps_prop and er1_timepoint2 objects
library(Hmisc)
library(reshape2)
library(ggpubr)
###PCoA (Hu method)
###Hu et al Nat comms.....canberra distance...
### OTU-based PCoA

##########Hu et al Nat comms.....canberra distance...
### OTU-based PCoA
#features with low abundance (<0.01%) were all excluded from the analysis.
ps_t <- ps_prop
ps_t<-prune_samples(rownames(er1_timepoint2), ps_t) ##Subset to needed samples...

###Filter...>0.01% (this is to keep....)
threshould<-1
tmp<-ps_t@otu_table[,]
tmp<-apply(tmp, 1, function(x){names(table(x>0.0001))[table(x>0.0001)>threshould]})
tmp<-unlist(tmp);tmp<-tmp[tmp==TRUE]
tmp<-names(tmp)
###Filter does 

library(vegan)
cts_fil<-as.data.frame(t(ps_t@otu_table))
mt<-cts_fil[,colnames(cts_fil)%in%tmp]

# dist_ <- vegdist(cts_fil, method = 'bray')
# eigen <- pcoa(dist_)$values$Eigenvalues
# percent_var <- signif(eigen/sum(eigen), 3)*100
# 
# bc <- cmdscale(dist_, k = 2)

###Method=canberra

distance <- vegan::vegdist(mt, method = 'canberra')

meta_sub_MM <- er1_timepoint2[rownames(mt),]
pcoa <- cmdscale(distance, k = (nrow(mt) - 1), eig = TRUE)
plot_data <- data.frame({pcoa$point})[1:2]
plot_data$Sample_name <- rownames(plot_data)
names(plot_data)[1:2] <- c('PCoA1', 'PCoA2')
eig = pcoa$eig
plot_data$Sampling_time <- meta_sub_MM[rownames(plot_data),"Sampling_time"]
plot_data$Microbiome_ID <- meta_sub_MM[rownames(plot_data),"Microbiome_ID"]

##Calculate ANOSIM to annotate...
library("vegan")
packageVersion("vegan")
#using rarefied data for this testing
set.seed(10)
ps_t2 <- ps_rarefied
ps_t2<-prune_samples(rownames(er1_timepoint2), ps_t2) #
###Add sampling time
ps_t2@sam_data$Sampling_time<-meta_sub_MM[rownames(ps_t2@sam_data),"Sampling_time"]

mtx_group = get_variable(ps_t2, "Sampling_time")
mtx_ano = anosim(phyloseq::distance(ps_t2, "bray"), mtx_group)
mtx_ano

###Beta dispersion....
print("beta dispersion testing")
###
ps_perma_bray <- phyloseq::distance(ps_t2, method = "bray")

# make a data frame from the sample_data
sampledf <- data.frame(sample_data(ps_t2))

beta <- betadisper(ps_perma_bray, sampledf$Sampling_time)
beta<-permutest(beta) #tests whether differences are due to group dispersions (if they are, then p will be significant)
beta

# adonis test, equivalent to PERMANOCA
###To test the significance of between-sample diversity alternation, permutational analysis of variance (PERMANOVA) was performed with the adonis function within the R (v. 3.6.2) package vegan (v.2.5-6)
adonis_tmp<-vegan::adonis(distance ~ Sampling_time, meta_sub_MM, permutations = 9999) 
adonis_tmp$aov.tab ##Not.....Significant....

plot_data$Microbiome_ID<-as.character(plot_data$Microbiome_ID)
options(repr.plot.width = 6, repr.plot.height = 4)
p_Hu_mtx<-ggplot(data = plot_data, aes(x=PCoA1, y=PCoA2, color=Microbiome_ID,shape=Sampling_time)) +
  geom_point( size=2) +
  #stat_chull(geom="polygon",aes(fill=Outcome1), alpha=0.3) +
  stat_ellipse(level = 0.9, size=0.7)+
  labs(x=paste("PCoA 1 (", format(100 * eig[1] / sum(eig), digits=4), "%)", sep=""),
       y=paste("PCoA 2 (", format(100 * eig[2] / sum(eig), digits=4), "%)", sep=""))+
  theme_classic()+
  my_theme2+
  labs(title = paste0('PCOA of HDMTX treatment \nR = ',round(mtx_ano$statistic,2),"\np= ",round(mtx_ano$signif,3),"\nBeta dispersion pval=",round(beta$tab$`Pr(>F)`[1],3)))
p_Hu_mtx
ggsave(p_Hu_mtx,filename = "Figure3_panelB.pdf",width = 12,height = 12)

Panel C

To reproduce this panel we need objects generated from Figure 2, along with panels A and B from Figure 3.

Show the code 
#We need the PCNSL_metagenomes2, er1_timepoint2, and ps_prop objects
library(Hmisc)
library(reshape2)
library(ggpubr)

PCNSL_metagenomes2<-readRDS("PCNSL_metagenomes2.rds")
######################
################
#############DESEQ2

#############DESEQ2

###Perform differential composition in terms of ASF, Genus and Phylum for antibiotics..
# DESeq2 Analysis
# Determine which taxa are differentially abundant at the ASV, genus, and phylum levels.
# 
# We referenced the following: https://www.bioconductor.org/packages/devel/bioc/vignettes/phyloseq/inst/doc/phyloseq-mixture-models.html
###Use counts data....

library(DESeq2)
alpha = 0.05 #SET significance threshold
set.seed(10)

# ASV Level
ps_deseq <- PCNSL_metagenomes2
##Subset to samples with 1 sampling...timepoint
ps_deseq<-prune_samples(rownames(er1_timepoint2), ps_deseq) ##Subset to needed samples...
###Add sampling time
ps_deseq@sam_data$Sampling_time<-er1_timepoint2[rownames(ps_deseq@sam_data),"Sampling_time"]
ps_deseq@sam_data$Microbiome_ID<-as.factor(ps_deseq@sam_data$Microbiome_ID)
ps_deseq@sam_data$Sampling_time<-factor(ps_deseq@sam_data$Sampling_time,levels = c("Baseline","After"))
###COntrast of paired samples:
##https://support.bioconductor.org/p/84241/
#Effect of treatment, accounting for the sample pairing:
deseq_mtx=phyloseq_to_deseq2(ps_deseq, ~ Microbiome_ID+Sampling_time)
#deseq_mtx=phyloseq_to_deseq2(ps_deseq, ~ Sampling_time)
##
geoMeans = apply(counts(deseq_mtx), 1, gm_mean)
deseq_mtx = estimateSizeFactors(deseq_mtx, geoMeans = geoMeans)
deseq_mtx = DESeq(deseq_mtx, test="Wald", fitType="parametric")

res = results(deseq_mtx, cooksCutoff = FALSE)
head(res)
res2 = cbind(as(res, "data.frame"), as(tax_table(ps_deseq)[rownames(res), ], "matrix"))
sigtab = res[which(res$padj < alpha), ]  #SET significance threshold above
sigtab = cbind(as(sigtab, "data.frame"), as(tax_table(ps_deseq)[rownames(sigtab), ], "matrix"))
dim(sigtab)
###12  13
resultsNames(deseq_mtx)
#[1] "Intercept"                          " Sampling time After vs Baseline"
#This shows the results available. Note that by default, R will choose a reference level for factors based on alphabetical order. Here "Baseline" is the reference level.
#corresponds to the difference between the reference level (no Baseline) and After

##This means positive foldchange is enriched in After

##Order by pvalue
sigtab<-sigtab[order(sigtab$padj,na.last=NA),]
sigtab2<-sigtab
##Export tables

write.table(sigtab2,file = "DE_otus_After_vs_Baseline_mtx.tab",append = F,quote = F,row.names = T,sep = "\t")

###Decrease in Akkermansia which has been inversely associated with obesity, diabetes, inflammation, and metabolic disorders.

##############################################Plot #####################################""
sig_otus<-read.delim("DE_otus_After_vs_Baseline_mtx.tab")

ps_prop<-readRDS("ps_prop.rds")
###Extract relative freq
ps_t <- ps_prop
ps_t<-prune_samples(rownames(er1_timepoint2), ps_t) ##Subset to needed samples...

###Subset OTU table....
tmp_table<-ps_t@otu_table[rownames(ps_t@otu_table)%in%rownames(sig_otus[sig_otus$Phylum!="Uroviricota",])]
dim(tmp_table)
tmp_table<-tmp_table@.Data
##Change taxa names...
rownames(tmp_table)<-paste(sig_otus$Genus[match(rownames(tmp_table),rownames(sig_otus))],"_",sig_otus$Species[match(rownames(tmp_table),rownames(sig_otus))])
#Transpose
tmp_table<-as.data.frame(t(tmp_table))
##Re-order rownames
tmp_table<-tmp_table[order(factor(rownames(tmp_table), levels =rownames(er1_timepoint2))),]
table(rownames(er1_timepoint2)==rownames(tmp_table))

er1_timepoint2_t<-cbind(er1_timepoint2,tmp_table)

er1_timepoint2_t<-melt(er1_timepoint2_t,id.vars = c("Sampling_time","Microbiome_ID"),measure.vars = c(colnames(tmp_table)))

er1_timepoint2_t<-dcast(er1_timepoint2_t, variable+Microbiome_ID ~ Sampling_time, value.var = "value",fill = 0,fun.aggregate = sum,drop = T)

p1_div_mtx_otus<-ggpaired(er1_timepoint2_t, cond1 = "Baseline",cond2 = "After", line.color = "black", line.size = 0.4,id = "Microbiome_ID",facet.by = "variable",fill="condition",xlab = "Condition",ylab = "Relative counts")+theme_std()+theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90,size=8),axis.title = element_text(face="bold"),plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5,face = "bold",size = 15))+stat_compare_means(paired = TRUE,label = "p.format",vjust=.35)+scale_fill_manual(values = rep(c("steelblue1","steelblue4"),5),labels=c("Baseline","After"))
p1_div_mtx_otus

ggsave(p1_div_mtx_otus,filename = "Boxplot_OTUS_MTX_6patientsPaired.pdf",width = 14,height = 12)

###Let's plot independently Bifidobacterium _ dentium and Akkermansia _ muciniphila


p1_div_mtx_otus2<-ggpaired(er1_timepoint2_t[er1_timepoint2_t$variable=="Bifidobacterium _ dentium",], cond1 = "Baseline",cond2 = "After", line.color = "black", line.size = 0.4,id = "Microbiome_ID",facet.by = "variable",fill="condition",xlab = "Condition",ylab = "Relative counts")+theme_std()+theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90,size=8),axis.title = element_text(face="bold"),plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5,face = "bold",size = 15))+stat_compare_means(paired = TRUE,label = "p.signif",vjust=.35,size=12,color="red")+scale_fill_manual(values = rep(c("steelblue1","steelblue4"),1),labels=c("Baseline","After"))

p1_div_mtx_otus2_2<-ggpaired(er1_timepoint2_t[er1_timepoint2_t$variable=="Akkermansia _ muciniphila",], cond1 = "Baseline",cond2 = "After", line.color = "black", line.size = 0.4,id = "Microbiome_ID",facet.by = "variable",fill="condition",xlab = "Condition",ylab = "Relative counts")+theme_std()+theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90,size=8),axis.title = element_text(face="bold"),plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5,face = "bold",size = 15))+stat_compare_means(paired = TRUE,label = "p.signif",vjust=.35,size=12,color="red")+scale_fill_manual(values = rep(c("steelblue1","steelblue4"),1),labels=c("Baseline","After"))
p1_div_mtx_otus3<-  ggarrange(p1_div_mtx_otus2,p1_div_mtx_otus2_2,ncol = 1,common.legend = T,align = "hv")
  
ggsave(p1_div_mtx_otus3,filename = "Figure3_panelC.pdf",width = 14,height = 12)
